## IV Conclusion

In conclusion, we report top grating, surface-emitting DFB QCLs at 4.8 \(\mu\)m operating in continuous wave at room temperature. For a 13-\(\mu\)m-wide and 4-mm-long laser, the CW output power emitted from the substrate reached 94 mW at heat sink temperature of 25 \({}^{\circ}\)C with a low threshold current density of 1.21 kA/cm\({}^{2}\). Single-mode emission with a side-mode suppression ratio (SMSR) about 30 dB is continuously tunable by the heat sink temperature or injection current. A far-field radiation pattern with a low divergence angle of \(0.58^{\circ}\times 16.2^{\circ}\) is obtained.

